<p>The&nbsp;map below shows the location of Davis Hall on the UC Berkeley campus. You can use this map to get directions or view the surrounding area. For further information on campus access and parking, see the instructions below.</p>

<p><br>
<a href="https://goo.gl/maps/P2utQ">View Larger Map</a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Access to Davis and McLaughlin Halls from Hearst Avenue</h2>

<p>Enter through Campus North Gate, located at the intersection of Euclid and Hearst Avenues. Take the first path to the left, which leads past Sutardja Dai Hall to Davis Hall. Turn left and go up the stairs to the main (west) entrance of Davis Hall or turn right to the entrance of McLaughlin Hall.</p>

<p>Alternatively, enter campus from the upper end of Hearst Avenue via the pathway between Sutardja Dai Hall and Cory Hall. Walk down pathway to the east entrance of Davis Hall. If the destination is McLaughlin, walk past Davis Hall, turn right, walk through the terrace on the south side of Davis and down the steps to McLaughlin.</p>

<p>Both entrances of Davis Hall are on the third floor. Enter Davis Hall and follow the hallway to the elevators. The CEE department offices are located on the seventh floor of Davis Hall.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Parking Near Davis and McLaughlin Halls</h2>

<p>CEE provides central campus parking permits to guests of the department. Two parking structures are available to those with a central campus parking permit. The closest lot is the <a href="http://pt.berkeley.edu/parking/visitor/lots-pricing">Lower Hearst Parking Structure</a>, located at the intersection of Hearst and Scenic Avenues. Enter this structure from Hearst Avenue. Read the posted signs as certain levels are designated for holders of central campus parking permits.</p>

<p>The <a href="http://pt.berkeley.edu/parking/visitor/lots-pricing">Upper Hearst Parking Structure</a>, located at the intersection of Hearst Avenue and Gayley Road, is also available for parking. If you park in this structure, enter campus via the pathway between Sutardja Dai Hall and Cory Hall. (See <em>Access to Davis and McLaughlin Halls from Hearst Avenue</em> above.)</p>

<p>If you are parking near Davis and McLaughlin Halls without a permit, you will need to park in one of the garages near campus, or find street parking. See <a href="http://pt.berkeley.edu/parking/visitor/campus-parking">Public Parking in the City of Berkeley</a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Taking BART to Davis and McLaughlin Halls</h2>

<p>The Downtown Berkeley <a href="http://www.bart.gov/">BART</a> station is just 1-1/2 blocks west of the UC Berkeley campus. Get off at the Downtown Berkeley Station, walk east on Center Street to the corner of Center Street and Shattuck Avenue. Go north on Shattuck Avenue for one block. Shuttles from downtown Berkeley to the campus perimeter leave from the corner of Shattuck Avenue and Addison Street. You want to take the Perimeter Shuttle to the North Gate stop. Cost is $1.00. Alternatively, it is about a 10-minute walk through the campus, and up the hill, to Davis and McLaughlin Halls.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>UC Berkeley Visitor Services</h2>

<p>See <a href="http://www.berkeley.edu/visitors/">UC Berkeley Visitor Services</a> for further information on tours, hotels, public transportation, and a <a href="http://www.berkeley.edu/map/">campus map</a>. Visitors with disabilities should visit the campus <a href="https://dac.berkeley.edu/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Disability Access &amp; Compliance</a> site.</p></div>
      
